HEADWORD: Stryphnic
<hw>Stryph"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
astringent.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, a complex nitrogenous acid, obtained by the action of
acetic acid and potassium nitrite on uric acid, as a yellow crystalline
substance, with a bitter, astringent taste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

